               <p>JOHN PATRICK. I saw the prisoner, Perkins, cut the string of the brushes, which hung at Mr. Olney's door, and Lazarus took them up. I followed them, and saw them bury the brushes in a dunghill. I then secured Lazarus, Perkins got away, but was taken afterwards.</p>
               <p>THOMAS MOODY. I am an officer. I saw the prisoner, Perkins, running away, and am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
